      <div type="commentary" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>This edition and translation is based on <ref target="bibl:Kosambi1955">Kosambi 1955</ref>; Burgess and Indraji did not read the inscription.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<ab>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  sidhaṃ
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  therānaṃ bha<app><lem source="#Kosambi1955">yaṃ</lem><rdg source="#DasGupta1949"/></app>ta-<persName key="pers:BhSiṃha">sihāṇa</persName>
	  ate-āsiṇiya
	  <lb n="3"/>
	  pāvaïti<app><lem source="#DasGupta1949">rā<note xml:lang="eng">correction by the editor of EI.</note></lem><rdg source="#DasGupta1949 #Kosambi1955">kā</rdg></app>ya
	  <persName key="pers:Ghaürā"><app><lem source="#Kosambi1955">ghaürāya</lem><rdg source="#DasGupta1949">ghapa<unclear>rā</unclear>ya</rdg></app></persName>
	  bālikāā
	  <persName key="pers:Saṃghā">saghāya</persName>
	  <persName key="pers:Budhā">budhā<lb n="4" break="no"/>a</persName> ca cetiyagharo
	  deyadha<unclear>ṃ</unclear>ma mātā-pita <app><lem source="#DasGupta1949">u</lem><rdg source="#Kosambi1955">ū</rdg></app>disa saha <unclear>ca</unclear>
	  sa<lb n="5" break="no"/>vehi bhi<app><lem source="#Kosambi1955">khu</lem><rdg source="#DasGupta1949">khā</rdg></app>-kulehi sa<app><lem source="#Kosambi1955">ha</lem><rdg source="#DasGupta1949">hā</rdg></app> ca
	  ācari<app><lem source="#Kosambi1955">ve</lem><rdg source="#DasGupta1949"><unclear>ye</unclear></rdg></app>hi bhatavireyehi sa<lb n="6" break="no"/>māpito
	</ab>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
	<p>
	  Siddham. This Caitya-house is the pious gift
	  for the merit of their parents and presented for
	  the use of all categories of alsmen, belonging to
	  schools founded by diverse teachers, by
	  <persName key="pers:Saṃghā">Saṃghā</persName>
	  and <persName key="pers:Budhā">Budhā</persName>,
	  daughters of <persName key="pers:Ghaürā">Ghaürā</persName>,
	  the disciple of the Reverend Elder
	  <persName key="pers:BhSiṃha">Siṃha</persName>,
	  who took holy orders.
	</p>
      </div>
